KEYS IN MAIN MENU
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Mouse or arrow keys to move
Left mouse button or "left shift key" to select
Right mouse button or "ESC key" for fast return from OPTION screen



KEYS IN GAME
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
Left mouse button to select the tile
Right mouse button to active help
Both mouse buttons to de-select the tile
P key to pause
M key to enable or disable the game music
S key to enable or disable the game sfx
Esc key to quit



FEATURES
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
15 different levels
Useful HELP mode for beginners
Automatic check of a premature end-of-the-game (no free tiles to remove)
32 colours screens on ECS machines
256 colours screens on AGA machines
4 different modules
Superb SFX
Full game loaded at start on machines with 1Mb chip or more
Hi-scores and setup saving
Possibility to load "new tiles-set" during the game



SWITCHES
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
.->START        To play the game.
|
|->OPTIONS      To chose your best configuration, and in particular.
|  |
|  |->MAIN MENU          To come back to MAIN MENU.
|  |
|  |->RANDOM GAME SCHEMES  To play with a random levels scheme every time
|  |                       you start the game.
|  |
|  |->HELP ON/OFF        To enable/disable use of the help-mode in the game.
|  |                     With HELP ON you will have 3 available help for
|  |                     each level but a lower bonus score at the end of
|  |                     the game.
|  |
|  |->TIME ON/OFF        To enable/disable the time-limit in the game. With
|  |                     TIME ON you will achieve higher scores.
|  |
|  |->SOUND ON/OFF       To enable/disable the sound in game.
|  |
|  |->MUSIC ON/OFF       To enable/disable the music in game.
|  |
|  |->LOAD TILES         To load up to 1000 new set of tiles.
|  |                     On ECS machines will be showed only the ECS set of
|  |                     tiles.
|  |
|  `->SCREEN SETUP       To obtain the best view of the game screen.
|
|->ABOUT        Some infos about the authors.
|
|->HIGH-SCORES  Display the high-scores screen.
|
`->QUIT         Quit the game and save the High-scores and the setup (if
                changed), then don't reset during the game!!!



SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

    Minimum configuration: Kickstart 1.3, 512K of FAST memory, 512K of CHIP
                           memory (I have not tried the game on kickstart
                           1.2, but I think that it works certainly)

    Memory needed on ECS machines:
    Minimum: about 373K of CHIP and about 286K of FAST
    With about 669K of CHIP and 286K of FAST or about 955K of CHIP, no
    loading in game (but in case you play the game from a disk, do not
    remove it from the drive!)

    Memory needed on AGA machines:
    Minimum: about 437K of CHIP and about 286K of FAST
    With about 747K of CHIP and 286K of FAST or about 1033K of CHIP, no
    loading in game (but in case you play the game from a disk, do not
    remove it from the drive!)



